                <td valign="top" class="mainbox"> 
				
				                     <div align="center"><h3>Help/FAQ</h3> </div>


<u>How to Apply for membership:</u> Click on the link in the menu to the left titled Apply for Citizenship. Fill out the application form there for your 
main charachter being applied. You must include a working e-mail address and at least one member of the guild whom you know and can use as a 
referrence. 
<br><br>

<u>How to Apply an Alternate Character for membership:</u> Click on the link to the left titled Apply for Citizenship. At the top of the Main Application page is 
a button titles Apply and Alt for Citizenship. Click on this button and fill out the application and submit it. Alts may not be issued an invitation to the guild 
until the main charachter has been in the guild for one weeks time. 
<br><br>

<u>How to Apply for an Officer Position:</u> Click on the link to the left titled Apply for Citizenship. At the top of the Main Application page is a button titled 
Apply to be a Senator. Click on this button and fill out the Application and submit it. Be sure to specify which position in the Senate you are applying for. 
<br><br>

<u>Member Login:</u> Upon being issued an invitation to the guild you will recieve an e-mail to the address you provided with your Username and 
Password. This is what you need to be able to log into the member only portion of the website. 
<br><br>

<u>Changing your Password:</u> To change your Password simply login with the one you were given or have been using. Click on your Main 
Character's name on the Citizens roster page. Under your Main Character's Biography field and Magelo Profile Number field is a field titled Password. Simply enter your new Password in this field and then click on the button titled Save Changes located under that. 

<br><br>
<u>Magelo Profile:</u> To enter a Magelo Profile on the Divine Sanction Website go to www.magelo.com and follow the directions provided there 
to create a Profile, each Character's profile will have its own number. To place your character's profile on this website click on your Main 
Character's name on the Citizen's roster and enter each character's profile  number in the field provided under each character's biography 
field. Make sure you click on the Save Changes button after inputting each number. To view a Magelo Profile click on the (Magelo) link after 
the character's name on the Citizen Roster. 

<br><br>
<u>Character Biographies:</u> To enter your character's biograhies on the website click on your Main Character's name on the Citizens Roster. 
There will be a large field for each of your character's biograpyies. Once you have filled out one character's biography click the Save 
Changes button under it. You can then move on to the next character. 
To view another person's Biography click on the character's name on the Citizen Roster. 

<br><br>
<u>Self Updating Level(s):</u> Each member can update their character(s) level(s) as they go. Click on your Main Character's name on the Citizen 
Roster and each character has a field to input your new level into. Make sure you click the Save Changes button for each character who's 
level you changed. It is important for you to update your level regularly to ensure you are placed in the correct Legion's Roster. 

<br><br>
<u>Message Board Help:</u> 

<br><br>
<u>Create a New Thread:</u> Enter the Forum you wish to post under by clicking on it. Then click on the New Thread option at the top of the Thread List. 
This brings up a window with a field for you to enter your Thread Title. After entering the Title click on Save in the lower right corner. 
This will take you to the Text Window where you type the text of your post then click Save in the lower right corner. 
<br><br>

<u>Post a Message on an Existing Thread:</u> Enter the Thread you wish to post in by clicking on the Thread's Title. Click on the Post Message 
button in the top right corner. Type your message in the field provided and click Save in the lower right corner. 

<br><br>
<u>Post a Reply:</u> Click on the Reply button in the upper right corner of the POST within the thread that you wish to specifically reply to. 
Enter the message in the field provided then click Save in the lower right corner. 

<br><br>
<u>Edit your Post:</u> If you read your post after saving it and discover a mistake or you forgot to say something you can edit your post. 
Click on the Edit button in the upper right corner of YOUR post. Make the corrections or additions you want in the text field and click 
Save in the lower right corner. 
<br><br>

<u>Newsletter Submissions:</u> To submit an article to the Divine Sanction Newsletter email the article to Lassra at hopespryngs@hotmail.com. 
Anyone can submit to the Newsletter, closing date for submissions is the 3rd of the month. 
<br><br>

<u>Event Calendar:</u> Anyone may plan a Raid or Event and post it on the Calendar. To do this click on the Day # you wish to host the Event 
on and fill in the form in the window that opens. Please note that you must be brief as the description only allows 255 characters. After 
filling in the form clcik the Submit button and it will appear on the Calendar with a gray line above it. The gray line indicates that an Officer 
has not yet agreed to Sponsor the Event. Now go to the Events Message Board and post the full details of the Event you have planned. An 
Officer will review the post and agree to Sponsor the Event as long as it follows the Guild Rules. If your Event is Denied the Officer will speak 
to you and explain why and attempt to help you correct the problem. 
<br><br>

<u>Website Comments:</u> There is a Forum on the Message Boards titled Website. This is where you can report bugs or request features for the 
website and add your comments. Please note that you may not get a reply on this forum but your posts ARE being read and taken into consideration. 



	





